text: Härnösand Cathedral () is a cathedral in the town of Härnösand in Sweden. It belongs to Härnösand Cathedral Parish of the Church of Sweden and serves the Diocese of Härnösand. The church was inaugurated on 28 June 1846. It was built according to plans by Johan Adolf Hawerman. The entire town of Härnösand can be viewed from atop the 46 metres tall tower == References == ==Other websites== Category:Church of Sweden cathedrals
